The demand for its Hopper GPUs used in the training and inference of massive language AI models  and generative AI applications helped boost revenue. The earnings also revealed that large-scale cloud computing providers represent over half of its data centre revenue. This proves the resilience of its business units for the immediate quarters ahead.ğŸ¢The collateral gains have spilt over to other AI stocks  such as AMD  Super Micro  and Palantir  which increased in sympathy with Nvidia's share price.
